<br>
It got annoying to the point that I was willing to contact some guildies that had a L54 warrior and see about doing a trade. Guidies would have rather have had me, and I'm sure the uber doodz I was grouped with would have prefered a L54 warrior in crafted mostly wielding inferior weaponry. Didn't get any response out of the group - they probably didn't think I was serious on it.<br>
<br>
Even after Necro/Guard opened and we took it, the group was freakish about me pulling anything out of some paranoia of rangers tanking.<br>
<br>
<br>
Just for the uber kewl uber doodz out there, it is ok to let the ranger tank at times. Especially if they've tanked that camp before. It definately beats sitting on your ass waiting for a warrior, paladin or shadow knight to show up.<br>
